# Az'arch package manifest (packages.x86_64)
#
# This file is consumed VERBATIM by the ISO build. It is organised in two
# blocks, split by the delimiter below:
#
#   1. STOCK ARCH  -- the packages the official Arch install medium (archiso
#      `releng`) already ships, in archiso's own order. Treat this block as
#      fixed upstream baseline: do not reorder or edit it by hand. To refresh
#      after an archiso bump, re-sync from /usr/share/archiso/configs/releng/
#      packages.x86_64 and bump ARCHISO_VERSION in
#      scripts/libraries/spec_stock_baseline.py.
#
#   2. AZ'ARCH ADDITIONS -- everything Az'arch adds on top of that baseline.
#      THIS is the block to edit when adding or removing components. Anything
#      pulled in only as a transitive dependency of these entries is an
#      "Az'arch Component" in the specification.
#
# Baseline: archiso releng 88-1. Note: dhcpcd (shipped by stock archiso) is
# intentionally NOT included -- Az'arch manages networking via NetworkManager.

# ============================================================================
# STOCK ARCH -- archiso releng 88-1 baseline (upstream order; do not edit)
# ============================================================================
